Here's a template for an informed consent form.

---

**Informed Consent for Participation in Linguistic Research**

**Study Title:** [Your Study Title Here]

**Researcher Information:** [Your Name and Contact Information]

**Purpose of the Study:** The purpose of this research is to study the Dutch pronunciation of Chinese learners and its correlation with perceived foreign accent.

**What You Will Do:** As a participant, you will be asked to read aloud and record specific Dutch words and sentences. The recording session is expected to last approximately [time duration].

**Voluntary Participation:** Your participation in this study is entirely voluntary. You are free to refuse to participate or to withdraw at any time without any penalty or loss of benefits to which you are otherwise entitled.

**Confidentiality:** Your identity will remain confidential. The recordings will be used solely for research purposes and will be anonymized before analysis. 

**Risks and Benefits:** There are no significant risks associated with participating in this study. While there are no direct benefits to you, your participation will contribute valuable information to our understanding of language learning and pronunciation.

**Data Use:** By participating, you agree that the data collected from you may be used for academic research and published in academic journals. This data will not be used for commercial purposes.

**Consent:** By signing below, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this consent form and agree to participate in the study.

**Participant's Name (Printed):** ____________________________________

**Participant's Signature:** _________________________________________

**Date:** ___________________

**Researcher's Signature (if applicable):** ___________________________

**Date:** ___________________

---

This template covers the essential elements of an informed consent form for academic research. You can adjust the specifics to match the details of your study.
